List all products user have access to. Records are sorted by `created_timestamp`, starting from most recent products.

### HTTP Request
`GET https://api.onvoard.com/v1/products`

### Returns
List of product objects.

### Arguments
Field | Type | Description
--------- | ------- | -----------
account | string | Account ID to filter. Used when organization manage more than one account.
keyword | string | Filter by specific keyword.
group | string | Group ID to filter.
tags | string | Comma-seperated list of Product Tag IDs to filter with. Use this to retrieve products from specific tags.
universal_id | string | Universal ID to filter. For example, `shopify:12345`.
platform_key | string | Platform Key to filter. For example, `shopify`.
external_id | string | External ID to filter. For example, `12345`.
created_before | integer | Filter products created before provided timestamp.
created_after | integer | Filter products created after provided timestamp.
page | integer | Traverse to specific page. Page index starts from `1`.
page_size | integer | Number of records you want to return for each page. Can be from `1` to `100`. Default is `10`.
